race.description: Tabtouch Punters Club Pinjarra Classic 22/02 Hcp
race.comment: Nice race to end the day and THE SCHOLAR (9) looks an exciting gelding on the way up. He's impressed this time in work, being gunned down late by an in-form galloper 34 days ago. Can roll across from out wide and now third-up into the campaign, he can go one better. QUEEN ARIA (8) has impressed either side of the break, flying home last start at Ascot to be 1.2L off the winner. Pike remains in the saddle and while she may get back in the run once again, the big track and extra 100m is right up her alley. DON'T TRUST JUDAS (2) stuck on well from midfield over 1400m on the Scarpside circuit here last time out. Drawn inside here and should get every chance after finishing behind a smart one last time out. SO NATAYA 6) wasn't far away last start when setting the tempo and can go close third-up with Parnham on board. HEY PINO (4) finished strongly last time out and the extra trip should suit. Can put his best foot forward.
